                      "player": "B",
                      "move": "Nb4!",
                      "commentary": "(Diagram 4) The logic behind ...Nb4 is not difficult to understand. Black has a massive lead in development so he seeks to complicate the game before White can consolidate. There is also the little matter of ...Nc2+ on the cards, which will deprive White of his dark-squared bishop and ruin his pawn structure."
